@startuml State Diagram - Cart Lifecycle
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam StateBorderColor #4A90D9
skinparam StateBackgroundColor #EBF4FF
skinparam ArrowColor #333333

title State Diagram — Cart Lifecycle

[*] --> EMPTY : Customer logs in\n(cart auto-created)

EMPTY --> HAS_ITEMS : POST /cart/add\n(first item added)

HAS_ITEMS --> HAS_ITEMS : Add more items\nRemove item\n(at least 1 remains)

HAS_ITEMS --> EMPTY : Remove last item

HAS_ITEMS --> COUPON_APPLIED : POST /cart/coupon\n(valid coupon code)

COUPON_APPLIED --> HAS_ITEMS : POST /cart/coupon/remove

COUPON_APPLIED --> ORDER_PLACED : POST /order/place\n(via OrderFacade)
HAS_ITEMS --> ORDER_PLACED : POST /order/place\n(via OrderFacade)

ORDER_PLACED --> EMPTY : Cart cleared\nby OrderFacade

EMPTY : do / Wait for items
HAS_ITEMS : do / Show subtotal + 5% tax
COUPON_APPLIED : do / Show discount applied
ORDER_PLACED : entry / Convert to FoodOrder\nentry / Clear all CartItems

@enduml
